main event: Three red and white circular objects were observed in the sky over Elkhorn, Wisconsin on May 29, 1957.
interesting points: The objects were seen visually for about 2 minutes.
The objects were described as being larger and different in appearance from normal aircraft.
The objects had a red and white color and exhibited a white light from the northwest and red lights from the south.
The sound from the objects was described as being dimmer than the normal noise of aircraft.
Other witnesses, a Mrs. and Mr. ----, also reported seeing a white light that they thought was a flare.
sighted object: three red and white circular objects
